67	What is the typical processing time for credit card transactions?	Credit card transactions typically process within 24-48 hours for ACH settlement. Real-time authorization occurs within seconds, but funds are usually deposited into merchant accounts within 1-2 business days depending on the processor and bank relationships.	processing	\N	{"processing time",settlement,ACH,authorization,"credit card"}	90	t	2025-08-02 00:36:01.783517	2025-08-02 00:36:01.783517	system	\N	manual
68	What are the standard rates for restaurant payment processing?	Restaurant payment processing rates typically range from 1.8% to 3.5% plus $0.10-$0.30 per transaction. Rates vary based on transaction volume, average ticket size, card-present vs card-not-present transactions, and the specific processor. High-volume restaurants often qualify for interchange-plus pricing models with lower effective rates.	pricing	\N	{rates,restaurant,"processing fees",interchange,pricing}	95	t	2025-08-02 00:36:01.783517	2025-08-02 00:36:01.783517	system	\N	manual
69	How does PCI compliance work for merchants?	PCI DSS (Payment Card Industry Data Security Standard) compliance is mandatory for all merchants that process credit cards. Requirements vary by transaction volume levels (Level 1-4). Most small merchants need to complete an annual Self Assessment Questionnaire (SAQ), while larger merchants require on-site security audits. Non-compliance can result in fines up to $100,000 per month.	compliance	\N	{PCI,compliance,security,DSS,SAQ,audit}	85	t	2025-08-02 00:36:01.783517	2025-08-02 00:36:01.783517	system	\N	manual
70	What is the difference between a payment processor and a gateway?	A payment processor handles the actual transaction processing and settlement of funds, while a payment gateway securely transmits transaction data between the merchant and processor. Think of the gateway as the "front door" that captures and encrypts payment information, and the processor as the "engine" that moves money between accounts.	technical	\N	{processor,gateway,difference,settlement,transmission}	80	t	2025-08-02 00:36:01.783517	2025-08-02 00:36:01.783517	system	\N	manual
71	How do interchange fees work?	Interchange fees are set by card brands (Visa, Mastercard) and paid by the merchant's bank to the cardholder's bank. These fees vary based on card type (debit vs credit), transaction method (card-present vs online), merchant category, and transaction size. Interchange rates are non-negotiable and the same for all processors, but markup above interchange varies by provider.	pricing	\N	{interchange,fees,Visa,Mastercard,rates,markup}	88	t	2025-08-02 00:36:01.783517	2025-08-02 00:36:01.783517	system	\N	manual
147	What are the industry standard merchant services commission rates?	Standard merchant services agent commissions range from $0.25 to $2.00 per $100 in processing volume (25-200 basis points). High-volume merchants typically pay lower rates (0.25-0.50 bps) while small businesses pay 1.00-2.00 bps. Additional revenue streams include equipment leasing ($10-50/month), gateway fees ($10-25/month), and residual income from monthly processing fees.	commission	\N	{"commission rates",residuals,"basis points","equipment leasing"}	95	t	2025-08-06 02:05:08.273522	2025-08-06 02:05:08.273522	admin-user	\N	manual
148	How do I calculate potential monthly residuals from a merchant account?	Monthly residuals = (Monthly Processing Volume × Residual Rate) + Fixed Monthly Fees. Example: $50,000 monthly volume × 0.05% residual = $25/month + $15 gateway fee = $40 total monthly residual. High-performing agents build portfolios generating $5,000-25,000+ monthly recurring revenue from 200-500 active accounts.	commission	\N	{"residual calculation","monthly income","portfolio building","recurring revenue"}	92	t	2025-08-06 02:05:08.273522	2025-08-06 02:05:08.273522	admin-user	\N	manual
149	What documentation do I need for merchant underwriting?	Required underwriting documents: Business license, articles of incorporation, bank statements (3 months), processing statements (if existing), tax returns (2 years), personal financial statement, voided business check, government-issued ID. High-risk businesses need additional items: merchant agreement, website screenshots, marketing materials, supplier agreements.	underwriting	\N	{"underwriting documents","business license","bank statements","high-risk requirements"}	90	t	2025-08-06 02:05:08.273522	2025-08-06 02:05:08.273522	admin-user	\N	manual
150	What are typical merchant account approval timeframes?	Standard approval: 3-5 business days for established businesses with good credit and complete documentation. High-risk businesses: 7-14 days due to additional review requirements. Same-day approval available for strong applicants with existing processing history. Expedited processing available for additional fees ($100-500).	underwriting	\N	{"approval timeframes","same-day approval","expedited processing","high-risk timeline"}	88	t	2025-08-06 02:05:08.273522	2025-08-06 02:05:08.273522	admin-user	\N	manual
151	How do I present processing rates to potential merchants?	Present total cost of ownership: interchange cost + processor markup + monthly fees + equipment costs. Use interchange-plus pricing for transparency. Example presentation: "Visa/MC interchange (1.80%) + our markup (0.30%) + $25 monthly = effective rate of 2.10% + $0.10 per transaction." Always compare total monthly costs, not just rates.	sales	\N	{"rate presentation",interchange-plus,"total cost","sales presentation"}	95	t	2025-08-06 02:05:08.273522	2025-08-06 02:05:08.273522	admin-user	\N	manual
152	What are the most common merchant objections and how do I handle them?	Common objections: 1) "My rates are already low" - Response: Compare total monthly costs, not just rates. 2) "I don't want to switch" - Highlight cost savings and improved service. 3) "My current processor is fine" - Show value-added services like analytics, faster funding, better support. 4) "I need to think about it" - Create urgency with limited-time offers or rate increases coming.	sales	\N	{"objection handling","sales techniques","switching costs","value proposition"}	93	t	2025-08-06 02:05:30.819955	2025-08-06 02:05:30.819955	admin-user	\N	manual
